{"id":14881089,"mediaExerciseId":"977d2b5c-761e-4f78-bbcb-ca3840b9c146","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612315,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":238,"solutions":[{"id":5977980,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This question asks **to determine what effect collateral has on bonds.**\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":30,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b2c784dca3dc277c1a302bb751c8a0d0/619a06cf4f97e83b7f105908a89158c0/lateximg_large.png","width":962},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b2c784dca3dc277c1a302bb751c8a0d0/619a06cf4f97e83b7f105908a89158c0/lateximg.png","width":481}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The holder of a bond has a lot of advantages from collateral trust bonds because a bond trustee provides him higher security.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b2c784dca3dc277c1a302bb751c8a0d0/badb239e517a04d71b70dc4be97e8f3d/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b2c784dca3dc277c1a302bb751c8a0d0/badb239e517a04d71b70dc4be97e8f3d/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's explain a bond trustee. It is a financial institution that protects the debtholder and increases the trust that the debt issuer will repay the loan back. According to this, **the coupon rate provided by the company can be lower.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":136,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b2c784dca3dc277c1a302bb751c8a0d0/c033ee616da0502e111f84475c00f004/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b2c784dca3dc277c1a302bb751c8a0d0/c033ee616da0502e111f84475c00f004/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"If the debtor pays the debt regularly, the company will not own this (collateral) asset. **The disadvantage is that the company is still not the owner of this asset but has to keep its quality and performance.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b2c784dca3dc277c1a302bb751c8a0d0/749c2670c94b49c4abbcf5901e048986/lateximg_large.png","width":1014},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b2c784dca3dc277c1a302bb751c8a0d0/749c2670c94b49c4abbcf5901e048986/lateximg.png","width":508}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"ab958d64-9bf2-4607-881a-717f5f0e1553","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881090,"exerciseName":"2","page":238,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"96824ca1-4824-4974-9d9d-557e9729d958","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-fina